This paper deals with image processing and enhancement, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) and Retinex theory also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The paper also involves experiments and evaluation, which could place it under the machine learning (cs.LG) and graphics (cs.GR) categories.
